Anonymous Mon 04 Oct 2021 23:45:24 No.42140383 Report
Quoted By: >>42140587
>>42140295
The thing about modern settings is to find gravity and importance in the little things. Everyone is walking on solid ground, everyone knows what a phone is or the Internet, but it's the ability to find something which resonates with characters despite the mundane that you can really do well in modern settings. Fantasy has a lot of magic and rituals to spice up your story, but in a modern one, exceptions for car chases or crazy shit aside, your scenes will always be very down to earth and very personal. Set the up right, find what makes the characters tick, make them tock with one another and you'll find modern stuff easy. Well, easier at least.
